{
  "id": 5132993816559616,
  "name": "Inline script cache",
  "summary": "Caches compiled bytecode for inline scripts to reduce script compilation overhead and improve page load performance. This feature allows the browser to reuse compiled execution data for scripts embedded directly within HTML documents across different pages and sessions on the same site. Cache entries are keyed by a cryptographic hash (SHA256) of the script source and the document's network isolation key.",
